  <p>These End User Terms ("Terms") govern your access to and use of OrgPulse, a Jira Cloud application provided by OrgPulse ("we", "us", "our"). By installing OrgPulse from the Atlassian Marketplace, you accept these Terms on behalf of yourself and the organisation that owns the Jira workspace into which you install the application ("you", "your", "Customer").</p>
  <p>If you do not agree to these Terms, do not install or use OrgPulse.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>1. The Service</h2>
  <p>OrgPulse is a team health diagnostics application that analyses engineering workflow data from Jira Cloud to identify dysfunction patterns and surface actionable insights for team leads and engineering managers. The application runs entirely on Atlassian's managed Forge infrastructure.</p>
  <p>The specific features available to you depend on the subscription plan associated with your Atlassian Marketplace account.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>2. Eligibility and Authority</h2>
  <p>You may use OrgPulse if you:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Are at least 18 years of age</li>
    <li>Have the authority to accept these Terms on behalf of your organisation</li>
    <li>Are a Jira Cloud workspace administrator, or have been granted installation permissions by a workspace administrator</li>
  </ul>
  <p>OrgPulse is intended for use by organisations managing software engineering teams. It is not intended for personal use.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>3. Your Account and Access</h2>

  <h3>3.1 Workspace administrator responsibility</h3>
  <p>The Jira workspace administrator who installs OrgPulse is responsible for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Configuring status mappings and issue type classifications during onboarding</li>
    <li>Managing which team members can access the OrgPulse dashboard (via the Access Manager)</li>
    <li>Ensuring that team members are appropriately informed that workflow metadata is processed for team-level analytics</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.2 Authorised users</h3>
  <p>You may grant access to OrgPulse to team leads and managers within your organisation. Authorised users must comply with these Terms. You are responsible for all activity that occurs under your workspace's OrgPulse instance.</p>

  <h3>3.3 Account security</h3>
  <p>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your Jira workspace credentials. OrgPulse does not manage separate login credentials — access is controlled by the Jira workspace permission model and the OrgPulse access configuration you set during onboarding.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>4. Acceptable Use</h2>
  <p>You may use OrgPulse solely for lawful purposes and in accordance with these Terms. You must not:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use OrgPulse to monitor individual team members' personal performance or to make employment decisions about individuals (OrgPulse is designed for team-level analysis only and does not produce individual-level metrics)</li>
    <li>Attempt to circumvent or reverse-engineer any aspect of the service</li>
    <li>Use OrgPulse in a manner that violates any applicable law, including employment or labour law in your jurisdiction</li>
