  <hr />

  <h2>6. Data and Privacy</h2>

  <h3>6.1 What OrgPulse accesses</h3>
  <p>OrgPulse accesses Jira Cloud data using three read-only OAuth 2.0 scopes (<code>read:jira-work</code>, <code>read:jira-user</code>, <code>read:sprint</code>) for the sole purpose of computing team-level workflow metrics. Full details are set out in the <a href="/privacy">OrgPulse Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

  <h3>6.2 What OrgPulse stores</h3>
  <p>OrgPulse stores only derived, team-level aggregates — never raw issue content. No issue titles, descriptions, comments, or individual-level data are stored at any point.</p>

  <h3>6.3 Data retention and deletion</h3>
  <p>Stored aggregates and diagnostic events are retained for 18 months. Uninstalling OrgPulse triggers immediate deletion of all stored data for your workspace.</p>

  <h3>6.4 Data Processing Addendum</h3>
  <p>For Customers who require a formal data processing agreement for GDPR compliance, the <a href="/dpa">OrgPulse Data Processing Addendum</a> ("DPA") is incorporated into these Terms by reference. In the event of a conflict between these Terms and the DPA, the DPA prevails with respect to the processing of personal data.</p>

  <h3>6.5 Security</h3>
  <p>OrgPulse operates entirely on Atlassian's managed Forge infrastructure. No external servers are operated by us. Atlassian Forge provides encryption at rest and in transit for all stored data.</p>

